text:
The unions of the owners of the stations, tankers and fuel distributors explain why & quot; the fuel problem & quot;
07 Nov 2019, 13:10 by Lebanon 24
In a statement, the unions of the owners of the stations in Lebanon, the owners of the tankers in Lebanon and the distributors of fuel went to the Lebanese public opinion in general to explain the truth as it is and to indicate that the problem of hydrocarbons has not been intentionally or unintentionally solved. All officials, most recently a meeting with the Minister of Energy and Water as Minister of Guardianship of the sector, we turn to the Lebanese public opinion in general to explain the truth as it is and to show that the problem of hydrocarbons has not been resolved intentionally or unintentionally because the officials responsible for its solution did not bring a full solution, but With half solutions and throw v Instead of implementing what the Prime Minister Saad Hariri has committed to the sector, in the presence of eight concerned ministers, to ensure 100% of the price of fuel in Lebanese pounds, it has secured only 85%, Moreover, the Banque du Liban imposed a commission of 5 thousand additional, and requested a freeze of funds for thirty days in his account, which led to an additional cost unbearable, and thus solved half of the problem, which prompted us to ask the Ministry of Trusteeship to resolve the remaining half of the problem, we were surprised to reject the solution during our meeting with them On Wednesday, more than that, she initiated populist statements "The problem is with the oil sector and has nothing to do with it, instead of contributing to half of the solution or asking the Central Bank of Lebanon to pay 100 percent of the price of the goods from the Lebanese pound to the US dollar and cancel the commission imposed by the bank and not to force the freezing of the price of the goods 30 days." He went on to the Lebanese public and the public because we are from him and because he is living more than 25 thousand families from this sector, "We confirm that we will complete the real bleeding we have been exposed for a month until the last breath, that is, we will continue to sell the stock at the stations until the rest of it runs out, Perhaps until then their conscience wakes up and believe 100% in the Lebanese pound the price of goods And cancel any additional expenses if they wish not to charge them. "
